                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-28" value="&lt;div&gt;The generic engine model that defines the rules, grammar, and base schemas. It dictates how models are built.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;" parent="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-26" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="350" y="-355" width="660" height="20" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-29" value="&lt;div&gt;The specific model created by the user or developer that operates inside the engine to solve a specific business problem. It is an instance of the Metamodel.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;" parent="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-26" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="260" y="335" width="660" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-30" value="&lt;div&gt;The invisible, underlying graph of data, logic, and schemas. It represents the &quot;truth&quot; of the model regardless of how it is viewed.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;" parent="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-26" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="340" y="-85" width="580" height="30" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-31" value="&lt;div&gt;The visualization model. It holds the coordinates, colors, shapes, and layout rules used to display the Semantic Model to the user.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;" parent="ez4ky4WJp2ajRVcOHQkX-26" vertex="1">
